 Some of the facilities at the Mbombela Licensing Department are not functional. On Monday their offices were closed and only the testing grounds were operational. ALSO READ:No clear answers in licensing saga Community members had to go home without renewing their driver’s licences, booking for their driver’s licence tests and car licence discs. ALSO READ:New license system causing headaches Joseph Ngala, spokesman for the City of Mbombela Local Municipality, said that they do not know when the system will be back online. “We are facing challenges due to the load-shedding; every time it goes off our systems struggle to function.
After we got the power back on Monday our systems could not work and this is why the offices were closed,” he explained. Ngala urged the public to be patient during this time.